=== Pronunciation ===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /θɪŋk/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /TINk/


===Etymology===
From Old English ''[[þencan]]''.

====Verb====
{{irregverb|'''to think'''|'''[[thinks]]'''|'''[[thought]]'''|'''[[thought]]'''|'''[[thinking]]'''}}
#''(intransitive)'' To communicate to oneself, to try to find a solution to a problem.
#:''I '''thought''' three hours about the problem and still couldn't find the solution.''
#''(transitive)'' To be of the [[opinion]] that.
#:''I '''think''' she is pretty, contrary to most people.''
#''(transitive)'' To [[guess]]; to [[reckon]].
#:''I '''think''' she'll pass the examination.''
#:''(transitive)'' To [[consider]], [[judge]], [[regard]], or [[look upon]] (something) as.
#:''At the time I '''thought''' his adamant refusal to give in right.''

